WHERE AI ACTUALLY HELPS

  • Sales and revenue operations that are stuck in inboxes instead of systems.

  • Support queues full of repeat questions from the same customers.

  • Intake forms, notes and spreadsheets that never make it into the tools you rely on.

  • Leaders who know AI matters but do not want another science project.

We start with value math, not tools: if a workflow will not save time, reduce cost, or protect revenue in a believable way, we do not build it.

PROBLEMS WE SOLVE

AI experiments are easy. Results are not.

  1. Sales teams spending late nights in email and spreadsheets instead of in front of customers.

  2. Enquiries, forms and notes that need to be copied into CRM, project tools and finance systems by hand.

  3. Support queues flooded with common questions that could be triaged or answered with a simple AI helper.

  4. Leaders who know AI is important, but do not have the time or appetite for long consulting projects.

  5. Teams unsure when a task is safe and sensible to automate, and when a human needs to stay in the loop.

Many teams have tried AI tools, but very few can point to clear profit and time saved. We focus on the real bottlenecks that hit your P and L.

Teach, Evaluate, Deliver: a simple way to make AI pay back.

THE T.E.D. FRAMEWORK

Valid Agenda keeps AI implementation simple. We help you build capability, decide what is worth automating, then ship a small number of practical workflows that pay back quickly and are easy to run.

  • Teach your operators and leaders skills and safe habits.

  • Evaluate maps your current tools and workflows and scores AI opportunities by impact, effort and risk.

  • Deliver uses low or no code tools to implement narrow, high value automations that you can maintain without a dev team.

TEACH AI Coaching and Workshops

Practical coaching that your team can apply the same day.

We help operators and leaders use AI in the tools they already live in: email, documents, spreadsheets, CRM and SaaS. No theory. Just better workflows.

  • 1:1 and small group coaching for owners, managers and operators.

  • Short, focused sessions on prompt patterns and workflow design for your real tasks.

  • Team workshops that leave people with saved prompts, templates and checklists, not just slides.

Ideal when your team is experimenting with AI, but usage is inconsistent and results are hit and miss.

EXAMPLE OUTCOME

A small sales team standardises how they use AI for discovery, email and proposal work. Each rep saves 3 to 5 hours a week and leadership sees more consistent messaging.

4 reps x 3 hours per week x $60 per hour is around $2,880 per month in freed up selling time from coaching alone.

EVALUATE AI Assessments and Audits

Find the few AI moves that are actually worth it.

Instead of a lengthy strategy document, you get a practical map of where AI can help in your business, with clear value hypotheses and a short list of priority workflows to target first.

  • Quick mapping of the tools you use today and the workflows that run through them.

  • Identification of repetitive, error prone and slow processes that are good candidates for automation.

  • Simple scoring on impact, effort and risk so you know what to tackle first and what to ignore for now.

You leave with a 60 to 90 day implementation sketch that your team can understand, not a binder of theory.

EXAMPLE VALUE MATH

If you automate just 10 hours per month of manual admin for three staff at $60 per hour, that is $1,800 per month in capacity freed up.

When the audit and first workflow are less than a few months of that capacity, the payback is very clear.

DELIVER Low or no code workflows

Ship narrow, durable workflows you can run without a dev team.

We build on SaaS and orchestration tools so that ownership stays with your business, not with a custom code base. The goal is simple: a small number of high value workflows that keep running quietly in the background.

  • Intake and routing for enquiries and forms so the right person sees the right request at the right time.

  • Meeting to system workflows that turn notes into tasks, CRM updates and follow up emails.

  • Simple AI helpers that sit in front of support or operations teams to handle common questions.

We call out maintenance overhead and likely failure modes upfront so you know what you are taking on.

Explore workflow ideas for your team

EXAMPLE WORKFLOW

New website enquiries captured in a form trigger an AI draft response, create a CRM record, and assign follow up tasks with context.

Response time drops, nothing falls through the cracks, and operators can focus on the human part of the work.
